&lt;p&gt;Permanent position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 1 Care of the elderly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen to join the team on ward 1 care of the elderly at Glan Clwyd hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ward is a 24 bedded, dynamic and fast paced Care of the Elderly Ward. The nursing team are proactive, innovative and have a wealth of knowledge in this specialist area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The teams role is to ensure that patient’s needs are cared for in the individualised way that they require, for example the needs of patients with Dementia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All ward nursing staff are expected to keep up to date with new initiatives and interventions. All of the team are supported to do mandatory training other courses which are relevant such as pain management and extended skills such as phlebotomy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Overall this is an exciting and interesting ward which will give the opportunity for professional development and specialist knowledge in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rhian Jones - Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Eaton - Deputy Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
